- app/api/v1/book.py

Explanation:
- The file app/api/v1/__init__.py shows that the book_api blueprint is imported from app.api.v1.book and registered under the URL prefix /book.
- The actual HTTP handler implementations for the book endpoints (GET by id, GET list, search, POST create, PUT update, DELETE delete) are defined in app/api/v1/book.py as the routes on the book_api Blueprint:
  - GET /<int:id> -> get_book
  - GET "" -> get_books
  - GET /search -> search
  - POST "" -> create_book
  - PUT /<int:id> -> update_book
  - DELETE /<int:id> -> delete_book
- Therefore, the file containing the implementation of the book_api handlers is app/api/v1/book.py.
